                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On their return trip to the United States aboard the <persName>
                        <hi rend="italic">Queen Elizabeth</hi>
                    </persName> (December 15–21), members of the Industrial Committee on Reparations
                    met daily to prepare a draft of the Committee Report. A preliminary draft of the
                    Report was submitted to Assistant Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_SCE1"
                        >Saltzman</persName> on December 27 for comment by the Department of State.
                    The final Report of the Industrial Advisory Committee was transmitted to the
                    Secretary of State in January 1949. The major <pb facs="0886" n="852"
                        xml:id="pg_852"/> recommendations of the Committee and subsequent
                    documentation on reparations policy are scheduled for publication in a
                    forthcoming volume of <ref target="frus1949v01">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi> covering the year 1949</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
